 in a credit club described in the next section (cuRcLuBl ), a dummy (number or thing that changes) 
 which equals 1 if the farmer said his reason for nonuse of (material that makes plants grow better) was 
 'Insufficient money' (NOCASH), a dummy (number or thing that changes) representing the (male/female status) 
 of the farmer which is 1 if the farmer is male and 0 if female, and a changeable 
 CMANURE representing application of poop/fertilizer I (apply fertilizer) which may either 
 be a substitute or complement for chemical (material that makes plants grow better). The price paid by 
 farmers for (material that makes plants grow better) is left-out because it is constant across Malawi, due to 
 the monopsonistic control of ADMARC, the parastatal marketing board. 
 In fact, previous studies that tested for a price response have shown no 
 significant effect of (material that makes plants grow better) price on amount demanded and even found 
 the wrong sign (Nyondo, 1987, pp. 116-126). 
 Results in Table 2 show that, as expected, access to credit has a very 
 significant and positive effect on the amount of (material that makes plants grow better) applied by an 
 individual smallholder. The signs on the significant (numbers that change/things that change) say that the 
 cash restriction decreases (material that makes plants grow better) use significantly, but membership in a 
 farmers' credit club increases it significantly. Also, the positive sign 
 on poop/fertilizer (online or paper form that asks for a job, money, admission, etc.) shows it is a complement to chemical (material that makes plants grow better) in 
 Malawi, probably for two reasons. First, richer smallholders can afford 
 to buy chemical (material that makes plants grow better) and also enough animals to make poop/fertilizer. 
 Second, farmers report that their soils need both chemical and organic 
 (material that makes plants grow better)s: chemical to provide nitrogen and organic to help soil structure. 
 The amount of land helped grow is linked positively with the total amount of 
 (material that makes plants grow better) (cFERT ); while it is linked negatively with the amount of (material that makes plants grow better) 
 
